Spirit kwarts 💕
Eindelijk! Na een lange zoektocht heb ik ze weer gevonden 😍.

Deze mooie steen heeft meerdere benamingen: Spirit Kwarts, Cactus Amethist of Zielenkwarts en wordt alleen gevonden in Zuid-Afrika.

De meeste spiritkwarts is Amethist in wisselende kleuren, maar ook Citrien en witte kwarts worden wel eens in deze cactusvorm gevonden.

Spiritkwarts heeft de juiste naam gekregen voor de werking die de steen heeft. Het is namelijk een steen die je geest (je spirit) in beweging brengt.
Het brengt je in contact met alle aspecten van je innerlijke en uiterlijke leven.
Het helpt je om beter te kunnen visualiseren en manifesteren.

Daarnaast reinigt en zuivert spiritkwarts je auraveld grondig. Zo kan het negatieve aanhechtingen en entiteiten verwijderen.

Spirit Amethist ondersteund je bij het hebben van een positieve instelling en het positief denken. Negativiteit, donkere gedachten en zorgen worden weggenomen door zijn mooie energie 💕

This week I have been doing something extremely important, #selfcare . Selfcare is important because it helps to show you, that you love you. It helps build up your self love. It was my birthday on the 15th March. I am a #pisces. I am a water baby, a water lover, lover of the sea. My full moon is on 17th March this year so tonight I am preparing myself for being at "peace" with myself,  I am recovering from alot of trauma, especially head/brain trauma. I am tired 24/7 because of it and my brain is healing, however extremely slowly. Too slow for my liking. I am forgiving myself for letting my accident happen. I am also forgiving myself for everything. Awakening is a powerful experience, very emotional. You realise your self worth, your opinions matter, your voice matters, your health is your wealth. I could have lost my life and that is a risk I will never take again. My life is precious. Now, I heal, I listen to my heart, I learn my skills from the beginning as I find what I once was good at, I struggle with now (meditation, sketching, painting, art). Some things need restarted, however it's a beautiful growth and another beautiful branch on my path. Everything has happened in my life for a reason and realising my potential, purpose and reason for being on this planet is emotional. I am truly blessed to have the wonderful life I have.  I am rich in love. I am blessed to have such loving people in my life, who have held me, while my wings repair themselves. In my little alter I have assembled, there is a pine cone. Pine cones have always been lying on my path, when I'm having a difficult or good experience in life. They represent regrowth, strength and awakening. I am awakened and I am proud of me. You too should be proud of yourself. These quartz crystal spheres really brighten up our day! 💖🌞 Quartz can be icy clear or have inclusions, veils, bubbles and various colors. It is also known as rock crystal, crystal quartz, universal crystal or clear quartz.⛏️ People in the earliest recorded times believed in the magical powers of quartz. ✨ Ancient Roman, Egyptian and Greek civilizations used quartz crystals as potent talismans. The word quartz is thought to come from the German word "quarz," and the word crystal comes from the Greek word "krystallos," which means ice. 🧊 The Ancient Japanese believed quartz formed from the breath of a white dragon, and regarded it as representing perfection. Quartz has been used throughout history in rain rituals, crystal skulls and spheres for crystal balls to predict the future since the middle ages. I had a conversation with a good friend of mine the other day and we realized that for some reason, part of the discourse in the spiritual collective has turned into a conversation of being asleep vs being awake. 

One of the things that has been shown to me is that we will never be fully awake. The moment that you feel you have awakened, you have fallen asleep again. 

The process of awakening, illumination, etc is a never-ending, ever evolving experience, just like the Universe. Just when you think you have mastered it and have seen all the moving pieces, your initiation into the next level has started (see physical representations of this in occult societies and spiritual circles). 

The moment that we turn around and refer to someone as being sleep, we ourselves are sleeping. We are asleep to the sovereignty of the other. To their unique and irrepetible soul experience. To their cause and effect. 

“Everything that I judge in the other, is something that I judge in myself…”

If we accept the theory that the Universe flows from the inside out, then by focusing on your journey and respecting the journey of the other, you are helping heal and influence the world around you. 

It is not your burden to be the saviour of the masses. 

But, this is a free will Universe, so do whatever you want. Food for thought…

FULL MOON IN VIRGO ~ ELEMENT  EARTH 18TH 0F MARCH
Analytical outlook, self-care.

Its that time of the month where it gives us all as a whole a chance to cancel, clear, delete. An opportunity to truly let go to what no longer serves us and truly forgive and let go of what needs to be forgiven, even ourselves.

Virgo moon, guides you to really shine and let the light in to help with your growth. It guides you to sit down and start reviewing your life, your expenditures and look into where its needed of improvement, may it be your work life or home life, or even self improvement. Because Virgo is an Earth sign she is connected to earth, grounding you and helping you to think logically but also reminding you how by working on you will make you the best self, being able to shine and share your gifts as you grow.

This Full Moon in Virgo is here cosmically to illuminate you and empower you to focus on working on your shadow self, dig deep to heal old wounds and work on them. It also will empower you to finish unfinished tasks or push you to your next ventures that you were afraid too move forward.

Full Moon in Virgo is reminding you to not be so hard on you, virgo can be harsh on one self and strive on perfectionism. Be gentle on you.

Full Moon In Virgo would like you to immerse within and ask the questions what needs to be addressed.

Questions to ask your self
1.Have you tied up all lose ends ?
2.Have you worked on your list to finish unfinished buisness?
3.Have you sealed all your old past wounds that needs to be worked on ?

Full Moon  Ritual
Dance like no one is watching, Release all that built up energy from the Full Moon energy. Twirl dance it out to your favourite tunes.
Write up your forgiveness letter, rip it up and burn it or throw it out, do not re read it.
Write up all that does not serve you, may it be emotions, things, people etc.
And lastly write up a gratitude letter, may it be your past homes, relationships or your greatest teachers. By doing this it helps you close the doors of your past.

Affirmation for this Full Moon
 “ I AM WORKING ON MY SLEF WITH EASE AND GRACE“

TIME TO REAP AND HARVEST YOUR REWARDS

The triquetra has long been used to symbolize the holy trinity but predates Christianity and its use as such. This symbol has been found in Celtic and Nordic inscriptions and arts as well as on Germanic coins and Swedish runes as far back as the 11th century.

Some modern traditions use it to represent the connection between the mind, body, and soul. In Celtic-based pagan traditions, it is often used as a symbol of the three realms of earth, sea, and sky. In the past, there has been speculation that the triquetra is a symbol of the triple goddess or was used as a Celtic symbol of feminine spirituality though no solid scholarly evidence has been found to date.

Full moons are the perfect time to release all that is no longer serving you. 
On the Virgo full moon write down a list of things you want to release from your life, followed by these affirmations. 

You can also honour the full moon by: 
- Journaling, writing down and releasing your emotions. 
- Dance and listen to music, really letting your inner child out. 
- Moon Gazing, lay under the full moon and watch all its beauty. 
- Take a salt bath or go for a swim, the moon controls the tide therefore has a huge impact on water. Embodying yourself in water on the full moon is a perfect way to honour it. 
- Meditate 🧘‍♀️ 

Full moons are also a good time to charge your crystals, the moon will absorb all their unwanted energies making them cleansed and ready to set your intentions into 🌕

Four years ago, I had a successful YouTube and FB channel about parenting a child with mental illness. 

I walked away simply because I made nothing monitarily and it was emotional to do. 

Liz and I would go live daily and talk about what it is like to be a teen with mental illness and a parent of a mentally ill teen. 

We were often keynote speakers at events about teens, parenting and/or homeschooling.

Today, this IM came across from a woman who ran across our YouTube channel. It turns out she is a therapist and isn't finding support within her own community.

This so warmed my heart. We spent many back and forth texts today. I read/listened to her story and only offered advice when asked.

I am honored to be trusted with deepest secrets and fears of so many.  I guard them carefully. 

We discussed which diet, oils, crystals and teas might help her child's depression and anxiety. 

She is so excited to try them. I can't wait to hear an update!

Rose Quartz for love, devotion, inner harmony and peace.

Clear Quartz for revitalising your emotional, mental, physical and spiritual well-being.

Fluorite for transforming negative energy in to positive energy, promoting peace of mind.

TAURUS CRYSTALS ♉️🔮

From April 20 to May 20, the Sun is in Taurus. Taurus is the second sign of the zodiac and it’s cycle starts in spring - Taurus season. 

Taurus is symbolized by the bull and is associated with the element, earth. Taurus is ruled by the planet of love, Venus. 

Taurus energy is generally calm, but has the tendency to become aggressive especially during difficult situations. During this time every sign of the Zodiac will be exposed to Taurus' energy. How this energy affects you depends on your personality and ability to adapt to the changes around you. 

Taurus season may be a good time for many to work harder on their goals, small and big alike. You can take advantage of Taurus' determined energy to focus on endeavors that would be beneficial to your long-term success. Taurus' energy and ability to get things done with intense focus and determination can help anyone who has trouble concentrating on their goals. 

However, if you feel that you are more attuned to the aggressive part of Taurus' energy, you might want to slow it down a bit during this season. 

Fortunately, there are stones and crystals that can help you out during Taurus season whether you want to take advantage of Taurus' energy to turn your goals into reality or you want to slow down a little and learn to appreciate the present moment.

💭 Healing Anxiety 

I used to be a chronically anxious person. 

Pretty much everything gave me anxiety. 

Going to school everyday. Going to work everyday. Any & all social events & speaking to new people. Doing/trying new things. Going on dates. Being at all out of my comfort zone. 

You name it - it probably made me anxious 😅

The worst thing about it all is, nobody knew how anxious I really was. I never told anyone or reached out for help. 

Why?

Because I thought my anxiety was normal. I never really questioned why I was feeling the way I felt on a daily basis. I also didn’t want people to know I was feeling this way, as I liked to play it ‘cool,’ and act like allll was well. Although that couldn’t be more opposite. 

My body was in a consistent state of fight or flight, and I went about my life as if everything was grand!

It wasn’t until I got really sick (which I blame my high anxiety/stress lifestyle for) that I was forced to start making big life changes! 

And I’m so thankful I did. 

Having chronic anxiety isn’t normal. Living in chronic fight or flight mode isn’t normal. You don’t have to live how I did for the majority of my life. You can heal this.

It takes 100% commitment and dedication but it can be done. I am living proof of that!

I went from being the world’s most anxious girl to the Queen of Zen who lives most of her life in a state of calm 😂

Yes, I do still get anxious. I’m human. But no where near as much as I used to. 

Now, when I do get anxious, I have a better understanding of why I am feeling the way I feel & I know how to better cope with it. 

I don’t let it control me or my life & it doesn’t get the best of me like it used to.

In my next post, I’ll explain some of the steps I took to heal my anxiety & how I started feeling safe in my own body. 

Slide in my DMs if you’d like to chat about some of the things that make you anxious and what you are currently doing to cope.

Remember, living in anxiety isn’t normal. You deserve a calm & safe life. I believe it is your right 🤍

When your eyes see something, the image is actually upside-down on your retinas. Electrical signals in your brain switch the image right-side-up. (Isn’t that freaking wild? 🤯)

The effect of these clear quartz crystal ball rings is similar. You can see a reversed image of whatever’s near the ring inside the quartz sphere. With these garden stakes, see how the red stake is not on the top when refracted in the sphere?

That’s because I use optical-grade quartz in these rings. The clarity and shape of the quartz makes it perform similarly to a human eye. 🔮👁

The ring itself is vintage, made of 14k yellow gold, and once held a pearl. I’ve made a few of these so far, and they’ve proven to be pretty popular! 🥰

🌟Chakras🌟

Chakra (cakra in Sanskrit) means “wheel” and refers to energy points in your body. They are thought to be spinning disks of energy that should stay “open” and aligned, as they correspond to bundles of nerves, major organs, and areas of our energetic body that affect our emotional and physical well-being. There are seven main chakras that run along your spine. They start at the root, or base, of your spine and extend to the crown of your head. There can be a depletion of energy flow or too much energetic activity in a chakra — each will manifest into different outcomes.
When a chakra is low in energy, you’ll have difficulty expressing the particular qualities associated with that chakra. According to Malaspina, a great way to promote balance in a chakra is to create alignment in your physical body through:

🕉yoga postures

🕉breathing practices to encourage the flow of energy

🕉meditation to bring about clarity of mind
